{"word":"ὑετός","slug":"ὑετός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑετός</b></el> <el>(ὑ¯ετός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὕω'><el>ὕω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>rain</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>pluvius</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:— <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>a heavy shower</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>nimbus</el>, whereas <el>ὄμβρος</el>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>imber</el>, is <i>a lasting</i> rain, and <el>ψεκάς</el> or <el>ψακάς</el> <i>a drizzling</i> rain, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> in <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>ἄνεμοι ὑετώτατοι</el> the <i>rainiest</i> winds, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}